{"type":"message","id":"0af43b31","parentId":"a8ed96bd","timestamp":"2026-06-13T16:00:05.225Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:500a1a24-2ac8-4b36-837a-43d940722302 Noticias IA y Temperatura Goicoechea] Crea un reporte matutino especializado para Kenneth (IA Engineer en formación). ENFOQUE: 1. TEMPERATURA de Goicoechea, CR. 2. NOTICIAS TÉCNICAS PARA IA ENGINEERS, con énfasis en: - Herramientas para desarrolladores full-stack (frontend + IA) - APIs y bibliotecas de IA para TypeScript/JavaScript - Integración de IA con frontend moderno (React, Vue, Tailwind) - Recursos de aprendizaje práctico para IA Engineering - Frameworks y herramientas accesibles para desarrolladores web 3. ANÁLISIO PRÁCTICO: Cómo aplicar las noticias en proyectos de aprendizaje. 4. RECOMENDACIÓN DIARIA: Una herramienta, tutorial o recurso para practicar. Formato: Breve, práctico, enfocado en aprendizaje activo.\nCurrent time: Saturday, June 13th, 2026 - 4:00 PM (UTC)\nReference UTC: 2026-06-13 16:00 UTC\n\nUse the message tool if you need to notify the user directly for the current chat. If you do not send directly, your final plain-text reply will be delivered automatically."}],"timestamp":1781366405214}}
{"type":"message","id":"4dee721e","parentId":"0af43b31","timestamp":"2026-06-13T16:00:08.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll create a specialized morning report for Kenneth with the requested focus. Let me start by gathering the temperature data for Goicoechea, Costa Rica, then search for relevant AI engineering"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"836c0565d0284eb9a76b17455b53c340","name":"composio__COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS","arguments":{"queries":[{"use_case":"get weather temperature for Goicoechea Costa Rica"}],"session":{"generate_id":true}},"partialArgs":"{\"queries\": [{\"use_case\": \"get weather temperature for Goicoechea Costa Rica\"}], \"session\": {\"generate_id\": true}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781366405231,"responseId":"gen-1781366405-dW7FAnEeWkk4aSlJqjhs"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5be610e","parentId":"4dee721e","timestamp":"2026-06-13T16:00:11.630Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"836c0565d0284eb9a76b17455b53c340","toolName":"composio__COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"data\":{\"results\":[{\"index\":1,\"use_case\":\"get weather temperature for Goicoechea Costa Rica\",\"execution_guidance\":\"IMPORTANT: Follow the recommended plan below. Extract steps before execution, adapt to your current context, execute sequentially with current_step parameter, and check known pitfalls to avoid errors.\",\"recommended_plan_steps\":[\"[Required] [Step]: Retrieve current conditions using WEATHERMAP_WEATHER (use the provided location text; present a clear place label and consistent display units).\",\"[Optional (if local-time labeling is needed)] [Step]: Use the returned timezone offset from WEATHERMAP_WEATHER (or a known offset) to label the observation in local time/day.\",\"[Optional (if the location text is ambiguous, not found, or results look mismatched)] [Prerequisite]: Disambiguate using WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION (select best candidate + canonical label), then re-run WEATHERMAP_WEATHER (same unit conventions).\",\"[Optional (if you need coordinate-based consistency and have an authenticated provider available)] [Prerequisite]: Resolve the location to coordinates using OPENWEATHER_API_GET_GEOCODING_DIRECT (choose best regional match when multiple).\",\"[Optional (if using coordinates for current conditions)] [Step]: Retrieve current conditions using OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER (pass lat and lon separately; keep units aligned with WEATHERMAP_WEATHER output).\",\"[Optional (if a short multi-day forecast is requested)] [Next Step]: Retrieve intervals using OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST (summarize by local day using the returned timezone offset; report day min/max and prevailing conditions).\",\"[Fallback (if authenticated OpenWeather calls fail or are unavailable, e.g., HTTP 401)] [Fallback]: Use WEATHERMAP_WEATHER only and clearly label output as current conditions (no forecast).\"],\"known_pitfalls\":[\"[WEATHERMAP_WEATHER] Response is typically nested under weather_info (and may be additionally wrapped); verify the path before indexing (e.g., weather_info.main.temp, weather_info.wind.speed).\",\"[WEATHERMAP_WEATHER] Temperatures may appear Kelvin-like; convert to the chosen display units before summarizing.\",\"[WEATHERMAP_WEATHER] timezone is an offset in seconds (weather_info.timezone); apply it when labeling local time/day.\",\"[WEATHERMAP_WEATHER] Can return HTTP 404 for some formatted place strings; retry with a simpler string or geocode first via WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION.\",\"[OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER] HTTP 401 indicates invalid/missing credentials (non-retriable); also ensure lat and lon are provided as separate inputs.\"],\"reference_workbench_snippets\":[{\"description\":\"Compute local-day key from a UNIX timestamp using a timezone offset in seconds (for OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST bucketing)\",\"code\":\"```python\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\\n\\ndef local_day_key(dt_unix, tz_offset_seconds):\\n    tz=timezone(timedelta(seconds=tz_offset_seconds))\\n    return datetime.fromtimestamp(dt_unix,tz=tz).date()\\n```\"},{\"description\":\"Aggregate a single local-day slice from OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST into min/max temp, condition set, and average wind\",\"code\":\"```python\\nentries=[e for e in forecast_data['list'] if e['dt_txt'].startswith(target_date)]\\ntemps=[e['main']['temp'] for e in entries]\\nwinds=[e['wind']['speed'] for e in entries]\\nconds=sorted({e['weather'][0]['main'] for e in entries})\\nsummary={'low':min(temps),'high':max(temps),'conditions':conds,'avg_wind':sum(winds)/len(winds)}\\n```\"}],\"difficulty\":\"easy\",\"primary_tool_slugs\":[\"WEATHERMAP_WEATHER\"],\"related_tool_slugs\":[\"WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION\",\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_GEOCODING_DIRECT\",\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER\",\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST\"],\"toolkits\":[\"openweather_api\",\"weathermap\"],\"plan_id\":\"87d9a78537414941b4431dd451524c58\"}],\"toolkit_connection_statuses\":[{\"toolkit\":\"openweather_api\",\"description\":\"Provides access to current weather data, forecasts, and historical weather data for any location worldwide.\",\"has_active_connection\":false,\"status_message\":\"No Active connection for toolkit=openweather_api. You MUST call COMPOSIO_MANAGE_CONNECTIONS (toolkit=\\\"openweather_api\\\") to create a connection BEFORE executing any openweather_api tools.\"},{\"toolkit\":\"weathermap\",\"description\":\"WeatherMap provides visual weather data, forecasts, and mappings, helping users understand climate patterns or track severe weather conditions\",\"has_active_connection\":true,\"status_message\":\"This toolkit does not require authentication. Tools are ready to use.\"}],\"tool_schemas\":{\"WEATHERMAP_WEATHER\":{\"toolkit\":\"WEATHERMAP\",\"tool_slug\":\"WEATHERMAP_WEATHER\",\"description\":\"Tool for querying the OpenWeatherMap API. Returns current weather conditions only — no UV index, AQI, or official alerts. Timestamps are in UTC; apply the timezone offset field before grouping by local day.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"location\"],\"properties\":{\"location\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"London,GB\",\"Redding,CA,US\",\"London\",\"New York\",\"Tokyo\"],\"description\":\"A real city name (e.g., 'London', 'New York', 'Tokyo'). MUST be an actual city name - NOT a placeholder like 'your location', 'current location', or 'my location'. City names must be in English/Latin characters only. You may optionally append a country code (e.g., 'London,GB'). For US cities with state abbreviations, use the 3-part format 'City,StateCode,US' (e.g., 'Redding,CA,US', 'Portland,OR,US') - the 2-part format 'City,StateCode' will be interpreted as a country code (e.g., 'CA' = Canada, not California). If a 'city not found' error occurs, retry with a simpler string (e.g., drop state code, use just 'City' or 'City,CountryCode'). Small or remote locations may return no data; handle gracefully rather than retrying indefinitely.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION\":{\"toolkit\":\"WEATHERMAP\",\"tool_slug\":\"WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION\",\"description\":\"Tool to resolve a human place name into canonical lat/lon coordinates using OpenWeather Geocoding API. Use when you need to convert location strings (city names, addresses) into coordinates for weather forecasts or other location-based queries. Returns up to 5 candidate matches; the first result is typically the most relevant.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"q\"],\"properties\":{\"q\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"Rarotonga,CK\",\"London,GB\",\"Austin,TX,US\",\"New York\",\"Tokyo,JP\"],\"description\":\"Location query string in format 'city' or 'city,country_code' or 'city,state,country_code'. For US locations, you can include state code (e.g., 'Austin,TX,US'). Use ISO 3166 country codes (e.g., 'London,GB', 'Paris,FR'). The API supports 200,000+ registered locations.\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"default\":5,\"maximum\":5,\"minimum\":1,\"examples\":[1,3,5],\"description\":\"Maximum number of location matches to return (1-5). Use this to limit results when multiple locations share the same name. Default is 5.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_GEOCODING_DIRECT\":{\"toolkit\":\"OPENWEATHER_API\",\"tool_slug\":\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_GEOCODING_DIRECT\",\"description\":\"Tool to convert a location name into geographic coordinates. Use when you need latitude and longitude for a given location after confirming the precise name.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"q\"],\"properties\":{\"q\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"London,UK\"],\"description\":\"Location query including city name, state code and country code separated by commas (e.g., 'London,UK'). Ambiguous queries can return multiple mismatched locations; use the full three-part format 'city,state_code,country_code' (e.g., 'Springfield,IL,US') and verify the returned country/region before using coordinates downstream.\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"default\":5,\"maximum\":5,\"minimum\":1,\"examples\":[5],\"description\":\"Number of results to return (1 to 5). Defaults to 5. Use 1 only for unambiguous locations; for ambiguous queries review all returned results to select the correct match.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER\":{\"toolkit\":\"OPENWEATHER_API\",\"tool_slug\":\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER\",\"description\":\"Tool to retrieve current weather data for a location. Use when you need up-to-the-minute weather inf...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER\"]}}},\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST\":{\"toolkit\":\"OPENWEATHER_API\",\"tool_slug\":\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST\",\"description\":\"Tool to get a 5-day forecast every 3 hours (up to 40 UTC timestamps). Exactly one location identifie...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST\"]}}}},\"time_info\":{\"current_time_utc\":\"2026-06-13T16:00:11.535Z\",\"current_time_utc_epoch_seconds\":1781366411,\"message\":\"\\n          - This is time in UTC timezone. Get timezone from user if you needed.\\n          - Always use this time info to construct parameters for tool calls appropriately even when the tool call requires relative times like 'last week', 'last 24 hours', 'today', 'tomorrow' etc.\\n          - Do not hallucinate the time or timezone by yourself.\\n        \"},\"session\":{\"id\":\"kids\",\"generate_id\":true,\"instructions\":\"REQUIRED: Pass session_id \\\"kids\\\" in ALL subsequent meta tool calls for this workflow.\"},\"next_steps_guidance\":[\"1) You may call COMPOSIO_MANAGE_CONNECTIONS: Some toolkits lack active connections\",\"2) Extract validated plan steps returned above, acknowledge each step, then execute sequentially updating current_step parameter. Check pitfalls during execution.\"],\"success\":true,\"error\":null},\"error\":null,\"log_id\":\"log_Gdj81j3rQsRA\",\"successful\":true}"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"composio","mcpTool":"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781366411629}}
